Songs from the Big Chair is the second studio album by the British rock band
Tears for Fears, released on 25 February 1985 by Phonogram Records. The album
peaked at number two in the UK and number one in the US. It spawned a string
of international hit singles, including "Mothers Talk", "Shout", "Everybody
Wants to Rule the World", and "Head over Heels". It remains their
best-selling album to date..
